    <item>
      <title>The Legend of Samus</title>
      <author>Samus_Aran</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/571123</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/571123#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a49ad95dc0a656ea95ddb2eb9ff2b80c2c6fa19f</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 20:52:13 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67a2e86225596.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688752947d81f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67b14b790b521.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688661396a2af.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68938b6fa5e2e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/679875c026681.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/679875c0e297a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/689af7d666ee6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67b65b6dde32e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67bf52a321a2d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67ac721d1c753.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67caf1027a2ce.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/689afa8a3b7d7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67d429e1cea4d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688753a8bc19c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6895846d9811f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; MISSION COMPLETE&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm going to have to take a break from modding for a little while. My daughter is about to be born in the next couple of weeks, so I'll have my hands full. Wish us luck.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Besides, there's not much else I plan to do at this point and I'm very happy with how everything has turned out. It's been fun building these mods and I may add some things down the line if I think of it, but I'm happy to say: Mission Complete. I hope everyone enjoys it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please feel free to check out my &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://www.patreon.com/TheOnlyQuarry"&gt;Patreon&lt;/a&gt; if you want to throw some support my way or check out my other projects on &lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://toq-games.itch.io/"&gt;itch.io&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thanks for playing!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/3xtbZJItcKM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Hello Metroid fans :)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;Ever wanted to explore the world of Hyrule as Samus Aran? Now you can!&lt;br&gt;Includes: Beams, Missiles, Bombs, Armors, and so much more. See full list below.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;RECCOMMENDED MODS AND LOAD ORDER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Other peoples mods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/552265"&gt;Arrow Bundle Multiplier&lt;/a&gt; (Optional)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/957663"&gt;Improved Invisible Sheikah Slate&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional. or &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/973742"&gt;Ra Powers&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/958211"&gt;Invisible Sheathed Weapons&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/666973"&gt;Summerset Voicepack&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/484227"&gt;Early Master Cycle Zero&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/466677"&gt;Samus Mod&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(REQUIRED)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/493411"&gt;Fusion Suit&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(REQUIRED)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/496551"&gt;Torizo Set&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(REQUIRED)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/476498"&gt;Wild Running&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(REQUIRED)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color="#6ee16c"&gt;My Mod fixes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/1387716"&gt;Crafting Project REpack&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;My Mods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/1498161"&gt;The Legend of Samus Breath of the Wild&lt;/a&gt; (Put after Samus Mod)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/1497838"&gt;Samus Mobility&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Put after Wild Running)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Other Optional Mods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.patreon.com/sockpoppet" target="_blank"&gt;Varia Suit&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional. Get it from the Cherry Oven.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/436412"&gt;Ridley Armor&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Optional. Conflicts with Torizo Armor.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/dl/964367"&gt;Remove Pouch and Belt&lt;/a&gt; (Optional. Conflicts with player model, but looks great when armored.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;FEATURES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Logo &lt;/span&gt;- Changes the title screen with all of the Link artwork to be Samus related instead. I used original game art and ran them through filters on GIMP to make them blend with the BOTW art style.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Armgun &lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;Replaces every bow model in the game with Samus' Arm Cannon and makes them shoot in a straight line. Affects enemy bows and Includes icons and descriptions too.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Beams &lt;/span&gt;- Changes the arrows to have cool new effects and descriptions.&amp;nbsp;Includes 5 different beam types and Hyper Missiles! Affects enemy arrows too.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Morph Ball Bomb&lt;/span&gt;- Replaces both bombs to look like the Morph Ball Bomb in the classic series.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Scan Visor&lt;/span&gt; - Changes the Camera to instead look like the Scan Visor.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Grapple Beam&lt;/span&gt; - Changes the Magnesis name and icon to the Grapple Beam.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Upgrades&lt;/span&gt; - Changes Heart and Stamina tanks into Energy Tanks and Missile Expansions&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Mobility&lt;/span&gt; - Increases jump height by about 3 times and removes stamina consumption from sprinting. All other stamina related actions remain the same. Put after Wild Running.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Armor &lt;/span&gt;- Replaces most of the armors in the game with either the Zero suit 2 piece, zero suit 1 piece, or Varia Armor. Most helmets are the same between varia suit and fusion suit. All of witch will have vanilla stats and can be recolored. This is intended for players who want to use Samus' armors but still feel the natural progressing of the game. Once you get a few armor sets, recolor them to tell them apart or mix and match them however you choose. Icons have been changed too. As a recent bonus, I made all armors upgradeable. Even the ones that normally aren't.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;Save File -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;I added a save file to the downloads for anyone that wants to start their game with the armors and armgun for either cosplay or testing purposes. This save file is optional and there's nothing stopping you from enjoying the game like normal. The file can be edited easily with an &lt;a href="https://www.marcrobledo.com/savegame-editors/zelda-botw/" target="_blank"&gt;Online Save Editor&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Included in the Save File:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;999 Normal/Fire/Ice/Electric Arrows&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;10 Bomb Arrows&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;5 Ancient Arrows&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ancient/Wild/Rubber/Phantom Armor Sets&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Samus' Armgun&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Motorcycle Unlocked&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Clarification about the mods on my page:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;I am not providing a copy of Samus mod or any of the mods not made by me. The links on my page directly download from the pages of the respective mod authors. The author list can be found in the credits section at the top of the page. I did this to avoid having to open up 20 tabs just to download this modpack and the downloads don't count towards my page. To reiterate: I AM NOT PROVIDING CONTENT OR MODS THAT ARE NOT MADE BY ME. That would be plagiarism. However, half of the mods are, in fact, made by me and can also be found in the normal download section, but it's not necessary to click on those links. Just use the "recommended" list with the yellow links. Furthermore, The majority of the Metroid related content is actually part of the Samus Mod. My mods just build off of that mod by changing colors, mechanics or file paths.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;INSTALLATION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;Install all zip files using&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/tools/12110"&gt;UKMM&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;by either dragging and dropping them or opening them with UKMM. Do no extract. The entire zip file IS the mod and only UKMM will work. BCML is outdated and will not load zip files. UKMM fixes a lot of bugs and these mods will work much better with it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Follow my recommended mod load order for best results. This has been tested on two of my desktops and my laptop with no issues.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One user has told me that they had issues with this pack and that they fixed it by downloading a version of Samus mod without the music files. I only recommend trying this as a last resort to fix crashing issues. Using UKMM should have fixed these issues already. Please contact the Samus mod author or the UKMM developer if these issues persist as I cannot do anything on my end to fix this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;*If you previously downloaded "Chozo Statues", please remove it. It causes crashes near the spring of power and other locations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Starter Save&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;First start a new game and then save it. This will be the save file you want to overwrite.&lt;br&gt;Install save file by extracting and overwriting the files in that new save file.&lt;br&gt;(ex. C:\Users\NAME\AppData\Roaming\Cemu\mlc01\usr\save\00050000\101c9400\user\80000001\1)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
