    <item>
      <title>Hyrule Rebalance V8 - Shield Fix</title>
      <author>Arissi</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/611328</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/611328#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">e1f98c75e7255d2dedc423449821b40875b227f0</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 03 Aug 2025 15:56:59 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688f86bb52de3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688f86bb9c2e0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/688f86bbb502d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hyrule Rebalance by Hollo doesn't account for the importance of the shield guard stat. &lt;a href="https://youtu.be/UKq7y_rNEmI?t=125" class="SelectedElement"&gt;This&lt;/a&gt;  video gives a clear explanation of how it works.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To summarize: &lt;br&gt;A higher shield guard value means that your shield will take less damage from weaker attacks. Ie: A Lynel can break a travelers shield in one hit but a bokoblin would take multiple because of the difference in attack power. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The game calculates whether to knock your opponents weapon out of their hands with a formula involving their base damage, the damage of the weapon they have, and the value of the shield guard stat of your shield. If a silver bokoblin with a dragonbone boko club is parried by a travelers shield it wont be disarmed, but if its parried by a Hylian shield it will be. Hyrule Rebalance sets the shield guard stat to 0 or 5 for most of its shields so this important part of combat is completely removed and many encounters become more static.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/hyrule_rebalance_shield_fix_5e038.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
    </item>
